The paper focuses on assessing the effectiveness of agile methods adopted by an organization, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of a framework for assessing the adequacy and capability of the organization to implement the method, which could fall under the cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-category. The paper also mentions the identification of principles and practices, which could fall under the programming languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also discusses the assessment process, which could fall under the software development (cs.SD) sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the importance of aligning principles with organizational objectives, which could fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
